{
  "$schema": "design-tokens-v1",
  "version": "2.1.0",
  "description": "SnapAccount Design System Tokens — Redesign 2026",
  "_changelog": [
    {
      "version": "2.1.0",
      "date": "2026-06-11",
      "decisionRecord": "docs/design/design-elevation-spec.md §1 (WP-T3)",
      "type": "additive — backward compatible, no renames or value changes to existing tokens",
      "added": [
        "color.text.* — semantic text tokens (primary/secondary/tertiary/disabled/onBrand) with light + dark values. Resolves design-elevation-spec T-6 and accessibility-standard §4: neutral[400] is text.disabled ONLY; meaningful text uses text.secondary (neutral-600) / text.tertiary (neutral-500), both ≥4.5:1 on their surface.",
        "a11y override applied during WP-T3 contrast validation: text.tertiary DARK changed from the spec's §1.3 value neutral-500 #64748B (which measured 3.75:1 on dark canvas / 3.07:1 on dark raised — FAIL) to neutral-400 #94A3B8 (5.71:1 raised, PASS). In dark mode tertiary therefore equals secondary in colour; the spec authorizes a11y to win on conflict. Frontend/mobile: separate tertiary from secondary by weight/size in dark mode, never by colour.",
        "typography.display.* — named display type tokens (hero/title/section) replacing off-scale magic font sizes (T-9: KFS APR 38→36, screen headings hardcoded at 28, section titles 20).",
        "elevation.* — five named elevation tokens (0..4) mapped to shadow.none/xs/sm/md/lg so mobile exposes them via theme and dark mode swaps shadowColor to #000000 (T-8). Replaces ad-hoc per-screen shadow objects."
      ],
      "canonicalNotes": [
        "Admin-only divergences are corrected in src/admin globals.css under WP-T1, not here (success→Emerald T-1, accent=Orange separated from warning=Amber T-2, --radius-sm 4→6 + add --radius-3xl T-3, --color-loan #EA580C T-5). tokens.json already held the canonical values for all of these at v2.0.0 — no change needed in this file.",
        "Implementation landed since v2.0.0: elevation slices S0–S5, the GSTN IMS inbox (docs/design/ims-inbox-spec.md), and the MCA edit-log page.",
        "GSTN IMS inbox introduced NO new token values: StatusBadge IMS map (PENDING→warning, ACCEPTED→success [text success[700]], REJECTED→error, PENDING_KEPT→info), GSTR-1A map (DRAFT→neutral, SUBMITTED→info, FILED→success), and DueDateChip deemed-acceptance urgency thresholds (≤3d→error, 4–7d→warning, >7d→neutral, past/swept→info) are all SEMANTIC RE-USES of existing color scales. Recorded as component-level mappings in component-library.md 'Phase 7 — GSTN IMS Additions' + ims-inbox-spec.md §4/§8 — not promoted to tokens.",
        "MCA edit-log operation badges introduced NO new token values: INSERT→success (Emerald green), UPDATE→info (Sky blue), DELETE→error (Rose red) are semantic re-uses of existing scales — component-level mapping only, not promoted to tokens.",
        "Rule of thumb applied: a fixed semantic→component mapping (status colour, urgency threshold, operation badge) stays in the component spec; only genuinely new VALUES (text.*, display.*, elevation.*) become tokens."
      ]
    },
    {
      "version": "2.0.0",
      "date": "2026",
